# Tauri Documentation

Use current Tauri v2 docs ‚Äî do not rely on training data for API details.

## Priority 1: Tauri MCP server

If the `tauri` MCP server is available, use these tools:

1. `search_tauri_docs` ‚Äî find pages by keyword; filter with `category` (`start`, `develop`, `distribute`, `security`, `plugins`, `reference`)
2. `fetch_tauri_doc` ‚Äî get full Markdown by URL or slug
3. `list_tauri_topics` ‚Äî browse topics by category

Workflow: search first, then fetch the most relevant page.

## Priority 2: Context7 MCP (fallback)

If the Tauri MCP server is unavailable, use Context7 `resolve-library-id` then `query-docs`:

| Source | Preferred Context7 library ID |
| --- | --- |
| Tauri v2 | `/tauri-apps/tauri` |
| Tauri docs site | `/websites/v2_tauri_app` |

Pass the user's full question as the `query` parameter.

## Priority 3: Direct sources (shell fallback)

```bash
curl -s https://v2.tauri.app/llms.txt
curl -sH "Accept: text/markdown" https://v2.tauri.app/<slug>
```

## Category quick reference

| Category | Topics |
| --- | --- |
| `start` | Project creation, prerequisites, frontend setup (Vite, etc.) |
| `develop` | IPC, configuration, debugging, mobile dev, state |
| `distribute` | App store publishing, installers, signing |
| `security` | Capabilities, permissions, CSP, asset protocol |
| `plugins` | Built-in and community plugins |

## Common slugs

- Vite frontend: `start/frontend/vite`
- Project structure: `start/project-structure`
- iOS development: `distribute/app-store/ios`
- Mobile dev workflow: `develop` (see Develop section)
- Capabilities: `security/capabilities`
- Configuration: `develop/configuration-files`

## Notes

- Tauri v2 supports iOS and Android in addition to desktop.
- For monorepo setups, point `frontendDist` at the shared frontend build output.
- Mobile dev requires `TAURI_DEV_HOST` in the Vite server config for physical devices.
- Use `tauri ios dev` / `tauri android dev` instead of `tauri dev` for mobile targets.
